        <content1 datatype="string" friendlyname="Heading">Welcome</content1>
        <content2 datatype="text" friendlyname="Content"><p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><span style="color: #000000;">For larger and more complex contracts APD offer a formal contract management service based on the "PRINCE" protocol (PRojects</span><span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #000000;">IN</span><span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #000000;">Controlled</span><span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #000000;">Environments). This was established by the Central Computer and Telecommunications Agency in 1989 and is a structured method for effective project management.</span></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm;"><span style="color: #000000;">It is a</span><span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;</span><em><span style="color: #000000;">de facto</span></em><span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #000000;">standard used extensively by the</span><span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #000000;">UK</span><span style="color: #000000;">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #000000;">Government and in the private sector. The key features are a focus on business justification, a defined structure for the project management team, product-based planning, an emphasis on creating manageable project stages and a flexibility appropriate to the nature of the project.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p></content2>
